\":\"772d22e3-7883-493e-8099-afd7cd2d7b0a\",\"slug\":\"carbohydrate\",\"title\":\"Carbohydrate\",\"type\":\"molecule\"},{\"color\":\"#ffed8e\",\"description\":\"Thermal cooking medium, enhances mouthfeel and flavor.\",\"image\":{\"alt\":\"$undefined\",\"height\":2400,\"src\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/g1s4qnmz/production/fa4fd23b7edcaf1209de0a94bf641b06d71e8fca-2400x2400.png\",\"width\":2400},\"key\":\"d4e35dd2-feaa-4c34-beec-d042892485ad\",\"slug\":\"fat\",\"title\":\"Fat\",\"type\":\"molecule\"},{\"color\":\"#ffd2a6\",\"description\":\"A building block of many foods \u0026 essential for certain cooking reactions. Sensitive to heat, salt, and acid.\",\"image\":{\"alt\":\"$undefined\",\"height\":2400,\"src\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/g1s4qnmz/production/e19eb6eaabe69b67347f7907a0014a9a3c57309e-2400x2400.png\",\"width\":2400},\"key\":\"84dd67bd-5d0d-4126-9639-138a4b2dec3b\",\"slug\":\"protein\",\"title\":\"Protein\",\"type\":\"molecule\"},{\"color\":\"#c1f5ff\",\"description\":\"An effective thermal regulator, heat conductor, and source of moisture.\",\"image\":{\"alt\":\"$undefined\",\"height\":2400,\"src\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/g1s4qnmz/production/d611d88f08f92f3706c3f7c36a846e1f774ede34-2400x2400.png\",\"width\":2400},\"key\":\"281ad9b2-c149-4e1c-8fce-777e5635b330\",\"slug\":\"water\",\"title\":\"Water\",\"type\":\"molecule\"}]}},\"preface\":[{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"f0bd55ffbd4b\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"9fc4da375ace0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Flour, water, salt, yeast. That’s all you need for one of the best vehicles for food.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"}],\"slug\":\"sandwich-baguettes\",\"steps\":[{\"key\":\"020681845ac9\",\"ingredients\":[{\"aromaProfile\":true,\"component\":{\"key\":\"7c09728ce42f\",\"title\":\"Baguette dough\"},\"fundamentals\":[],\"groceryAisle\":\"Pantry\",\"key\":\"01c53d42-2028-4f9f-a196-08ec9ad5d52e\",\"note\":\"$undefined\",\"quantity\":{\"amount\":5,\"label\":\"5 g\",\"unit\":\"gram\",\"alternative\":\"$undefined\"},\"title\":\"Instant yeast\"},{\"aromaProfile\":false,\"component\":{\"key\":\"7c09728ce42f\",\"title\":\"Baguette dough\"},\"fundamentals\":[],\"groceryAisle\":\"Beverages\",\"key\":\"92205637-4637-456f-bb35-b168361ef330\",\"note\":\"warm, around 105-115°F\",\"quantity\":{\"amount\":375,\"label\":\"375 g\",\"unit\":\"gram\",\"alternative\":\"$undefined\"},\"title\":\"Water\"},{\"aromaProfile\":true,\"component\":{\"key\":\"7c09728ce42f\",\"title\":\"Baguette dough\"},\"fundamentals\":[],\"groceryAisle\":\"Pantry\",\"key\":\"33193d63-1c8c-4025-a52e-92ece511cae7\",\"note\":\"or all-purpose\",\"quantity\":{\"amount\":500,\"label\":\"500 g\",\"unit\":\"gram\",\"alternative\":\"$undefined\"},\"title\":\"Bread flour\"},{\"aromaProfile\":false,\"component\":{\"key\":\"7c09728ce42f\",\"title\":\"Baguette dough\"},\"fundamentals\":[{\"color\":\"#c8deda\",\"description\":\"Adds saltiness \u0026 enhances flavors.\",\"key\":\"e5c329bf-a32e-4c6a-a893-4988340fddea\",\"slug\":\"taste#salty\",\"type\":\"flavorProperty\",\"title\":\"Salty\"}],\"groceryAisle\":\"Pantry\",\"key\":\"61e9225f-3a15-4ead-a35a-02c11db366c3\",\"note\":\"$undefined\",\"quantity\":{\"amount\":10,\"label\":\"10 g\",\"unit\":\"gram\",\"alternative\":\"$undefined\"},\"title\":\"Salt\"}],\"instructions\":[{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"1227512f60a7\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"9040b613c2bc\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Add the yeast to the warm water along with a spoonful of the flour. Stir until dissolved. Let stand for 5 minutes until light foam surfaces and little bubbles are visible.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"8eb8d42639a7\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"a35b83fd41d30\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note:\"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"b0cc4210d702\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\" Proofing is done to test the viability of the yeast. If there is no foam surface or little bubbles the yeast is likely dead and should be discarded for new yeast.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"1307b4f858d1\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"65d26adf4ff60\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Meanwhile, add the flour, and salt to a large mixing bowl. Once the yeast is proofed, pour in the mixture and vigorously mix the dough with your hands until no dry flour remains in the bowl and a cohesive mass forms, about 2 minutes. The dough will be very sticky. Cover with plastic wrap and let rest for 15 minutes.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"e3eea708f995\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"7c63455506af0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note:\"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"c67fa2960ce1\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\" Resting will allow the flour to start hydrating all on its own, and make the dough a little bit easier to work with when we start stretching and folding\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1}],\"slug\":\"mix-the-dough\",\"title\":\"Mix the dough\"},{\"key\":\"467d410095b7\",\"ingredients\":[{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"6db24a5a5431\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"mixed dough\"}],\"instructions\":[{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"e16b4d50962f\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"c6b1ef721d390\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Once rested, perform a stretch-and-fold by grabbing a corner of the dough in the bowl, lift straight up to stretch the dough as high as it will go without tearing, and fold over to the other side. Rotate the bowl and perform three more reps of stretch and folds. Once folded, turn the dough over onto itself, cover, and let rest for another 25-30 minutes. \"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"daaff91851a8\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"b1e49fc72447\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"This is one set of stretch-and-folds, perform 3 more sets with 25-30 minutes rest in between.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"a437e098115b\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"48d53eb71c8d0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"For each stretch and fold set, the dough should feel more elastic and stretch further without tearing with some air bubbles present\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"ddf22901a733\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"565622a229ce0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note: The stretch and fold method is better suited than \"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"7bc95a446b1b\",\"marks\":[\"0f52ea8faff9\"],\"text\":\"kneading\"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"111b7cf46be3\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\" for a high-hydration dough such as this because the dough is naturally sticky and this method reduces hand contact. Additionally, the stretch and fold will allow for an open crumb when baked because the air isn’t pushed out of the dough.\"}],\"markDefs\":[{\"_type\":\"fundamentalsReference\",\"_key\":\"0f52ea8faff9\",\"reference\":{\"color\":null,\"description\":\"Stretching and folding dough to strengthen its gluten network.\",\"image\":{\"alt\":null,\"height\":2400,\"src\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/g1s4qnmz/production/1d3ca0f7faf8f04c0b0f0ee136c2a0060baeecde-2400x2400.png\",\"width\":2400},\"slug\":\"knead\",\"title\":\"Knead\",\"type\":\"technique\"}}],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"f2af03e5700a\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"69d7efe66e170\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"After the final set of stretch-and-folds, test for gluten development by stretching up the dough very thin to see if it is slightly translucent before tearing.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"34873a7dc5bb\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"06b931c46d320\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note: The \"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"7bdb6a4b519b\",\"marks\":[\"db15cff47e2a\"],\"text\":\"gluten window test\"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"d71b4738122a\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\" is the key to understanding if the flour has been hydrated enough. If the dough tears before getting to a slightly translucent window, let rest for another 25 minutes and perform another set of stretch and folds.\"}],\"markDefs\":[{\"_type\":\"fundamentalsReference\",\"_key\":\"db15cff47e2a\",\"reference\":{\"color\":null,\"description\":\"Stretching a thin piece of dough to see if it's kneaded enough.\",\"image\":{\"alt\":null,\"height\":2400,\"src\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/g1s4qnmz/production/a4fe3347a7ce4ad96327ec5a9d7e69202f1430c1-2400x2400.png\",\"width\":2400},\"slug\":\"gluten-window-test\",\"title\":\"Gluten Window Test\",\"type\":\"technique\"}}],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1}],\"slug\":\"bulk-ferment-1st-ferment-stretch-and-folds\",\"title\":\" Bulk ferment (1st ferment) + stretch \u0026 folds\"},{\"key\":\"746cbf8bd007\",\"ingredients\":[{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"d7f11c719da3\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"Stretch \u0026 folded dough\"},{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"41a95853e8f1\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"Parchment paper\"},{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"f1e67e91afb2\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"Baking spray\"}],\"instructions\":[{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"dba2bdecad81\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"1bbe5348fd3f0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"After the last stretch and fold, sprinkle some flour on the work surface. Using a bench scraper, divide the dough into 6 equal portions (roughly 145-150 grams each). Cover the dough pieces with a clean towel and let rest for 15 minutes.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"2b804db02931\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"5a4108b0277e0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Once rested, spritz some baking spray on your hands, the work surface, and the piece of dough.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"c61c2ae6df41\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"44038da87fa10\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Shaping instructions: Using your fingertips lightly press and stretch a piece of dough into a rectangle about 6 inches wide. Fold the top edge of the dough down to the center, pressing lightly to tighten the dough and form an edge. Fold the dough in half to form a seam at the bottom of the dough. Using the heel of your hand, lightly press to seal the dough seam. \"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"9fe71d28ae48\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"eba80ad72762\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Now you should have a log of dough, and seal side down. Applying even pressure with the palm of your hands in the center of the dough begin gently rolling the log out into a cylinder, about 7 inches long. \"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"d6bfb84a3ace\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"debf6b5f268d\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Now place a hand on each end of the dough with harder pressure and roll the dough in the opposite direction with each to create a tapered baguette with a twist.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"a710c92877ea\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"ea8080fd38dd0\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note: For a visual shaping guide, look at \"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"66f87de3463a\",\"marks\":[\"fee0ce424c71\"],\"text\":\"the video\"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"18936d312d6b\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\".\"}],\"markDefs\":[{\"_type\":\"link\",\"_key\":\"fee0ce424c71\",\"blank\":true,\"href\":\"https://youtu.be/efqe9Umxopc?feature=shared\u0026t=386\"}],\"style\":\"normal\",\"listItem\":\"bullet\",\"level\":1},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"2a1ff8cc8d6d\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"7419371622b90\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Shape each baguette and place on a baking sheet-sized piece of parchment paper. 2 pieces of parchment paper, 3 baguettes on each. Cover with a towel and let it proof until about 1.5 times in size, about 45-60 minutes.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"650b60ad7def\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"6423f4cf32310\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"}],\"slug\":\"divide-dough-shape-baguettes-proof-2nd-ferment\",\"title\":\"Divide dough + shape baguettes + proof (2nd ferment)\"},{\"key\":\"e671224aec57\",\"ingredients\":[{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"53ddcdc17f75\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"9x13 pan filled with water\"},{\"component\":\"$undefined\",\"key\":\"8fcd4132c8b3\",\"quantity\":\"$undefined\",\"title\":\"baking sheet\"}],\"instructions\":[{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"3014c7ae0d20\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"d8ab825fd3a3\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"With 15 minutes of proofing left, preheat the oven to 450°F/232°C on the convection setting or 475°F/246°C on a standard setting. \"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"ddc6691bc8f4\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"f08ea69f73fa\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Fill a 13x9 inch baking pan halfway with water and place on the bottom rack of the oven. Place a metal baking sheet on the middle rack.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"normal\"},{\"_type\":\"block\",\"_key\":\"dfc5f93d0e90\",\"children\":[{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"9b35bb8738d60\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"Note: \"},{\"_type\":\"span\",\"_key\":\"492ddabf0fca\",\"marks\":[],\"text\":\"The pan of water will help create a steamy environment for a crisper crust and the baking sheet will be preheated so the baguettes can be slid on with the parchment paper and immediately start baking for faster oven spring.\"}],\"markDefs\":[],\"style\":\"no